Cameras:
ADS will provide and install a total of 3 cameras, as outlined on the attached schedules and maps.
Cabling and rough in will be done by construction trades as indicated on the schedule. ADS will provide
the cameras, mounts, licenses and patch cables. ADS will be responsible for installation of all devices. A
factory terminated patch cable will be used from the switch to patch panel.
Prevailing Wage rates have been included in this proposal.
Camera/Software Setup
A Enter the Camera Number in the Name and Location fields.
A Cameras should be set to motion and analytics (where applicable) at approximately 10 fps.
A Cropping out unwanted motion is the responsibility of LSR7. (flag poles, trees, streets in
background, etc)
A Modifying Users/Groups/Saved Views and Client software is the responsibility of LSR7.
Access Control:
ADS will provide and install 6 doors with varying levels of access control, outlined on the attached
schedule and maps. Installation will be provided by the company providing the hardware (varies by
opening). Cabling will be provided other trades as indicated on the attached schedule. ADS has
included time to pre-wire the door frames, and terminate the cabling to the hardware. ADS will also be
responsible for programming all hardware into the ACM software.
Door/Software Setup
A Enter the Door Number in the Name, Alt Name and Location fields.
A All openings (even contact only), should be programmed as Doors, not Inputs.
A Doors with multiple electrified leaves should be programmed as follows:
A Upon a Grant, a single leaf will unlock (ADA leaf or nearest leaf).
A Upon an Unlock, all leaves will unlock.
A Doors with ADA operators should be programmed as follows:
A The exterior button will only be operational upon a valid Grant, or when the doors are in
an Unlocked state.
A The interior button will always be active, but first unlock the door, then trigger the
operator to open the door.
A Modifying Users/Groups/Roles/Schedules, etc is the responsibility of LSR7.
